description:
Our client is a Chinese e-commerce, retail and technology conglomerate is seeking for a Procurement Assistant to support their daily operations.

Responsibilities:

Hands on source-to-pay procurement process with multiple categories focus (mainly in IT & Telcom, Facility Services & Marketing Services) via in-house group procurement platform.
Provides full process support with internal stakeholders and external suppliers in order to achieve business targets by implementing sourcing & procurement execution within the group procurement policy and procedures. 
Keep constant collaboration with central Group Procurement team in Hangzhou, as well as other regional teams, to maintain the synergy of category strategies, process improvement, and best practice sharing of overseas procurement operation.
Collaborates with other functions such as Finance, Legal, HR in maintaining overall process control and mutual key performance metrics.
Executing project-based sourcing with guidance of the line manager. Develop local category strategy and expand local supply base.
Requirements and Qualifications:

At least one year working experience in supply chain or procurement related industry;
Bachelor degree in supply chain, business management, finance, or related disciplines.
Fast learning in a very dynamic and fast pace environment;
Patient with sense of customer care, open-minded and willing to pro-actively communicate with others;
Proficient English and Mandarin, other language is a plus;
Familiar with online procurement tools as well as major IT tools. Advance user of Excel and Power Point, or database tools is a plus;
To apply for this position, please click on “Apply Now” bottom.  All applications will be treated in strict confidence, and used for recruitment purposes only in accordance with PERSOLKELLY Hong Kong Limited’s Privacy Notice.

Responsibilities 
Participate on project execution;
Assist on performance reporting and automation on reports to improve efficiency;
Support on planning delivery schedule on stock replenishment to China;
Participate on preparing flowchart of processes, user guide and training material;
Work closely with other departments to follow up logistics processes;
Provide ad hoc support to managers.

Requirements


Degree holder in Logistics or supply chain disciplines;
1 year or above logistics working experience, familiar with operations on cross-border e-commerce trade to China is preferable;
Independent, self-motivated and good team-player;
Good communication skills in written and spoken Cantonese, English and Mandarin;
Proficient PC skills, Word and Excel, acknowledge of SAP & VBA & Macro is preferable;
Immediate available is an advantage.

We offer

5 - day work week
Medical Benefits
Annual Merit Bonus
Staff Purchase Discounts
Staff Recreation Activity
Shuttle Bus Service
Education Sponsorship

