Responsibilities:

Collaborate with teams to develop eCommerce business for Asia Pacific including, business planning, content strategy and development, promotional campaigns and online marketing, website design, customer service, web analytics, etc.;
Act as a project manager to evaluate, prioritize, develop, manage, implement and test eCommerce initiatives;
Accountable for eCommerce sales performance of APAC (except Japan and Taiwan).
Share best practice with Headquarter digital team
Responsible for managing the entire process of the eCommerce platforms enhancement project, including improving the user experience, omni-channel development, especially for future projects O2O (Online to Offline, Ship from store)  etc.;
Partner with external vendor and Headquarter & local IT Departments to further improve the design, engineering, UX/UI, logistics of the e-Commerce platforms;
Act as a leader on e-merchandising with P.I.M (Quable) tool;
Establish a logistic flow with Logistics Department, external vendor and IT team for stock transfer; monitor and control the related costs;
Work with different departments on preparing sales forecast, pricing, marketing and merchandising strategies;
Keep track of daily and monthly sales, sell-through, inventory level, etc.  Implement contingency plan(s) if KPIs and Campaign ROI fall behind required standard;
Closely work with Digital Marketing Team for planning and executing digital marketing strategies including but not limited to website optimization, SEM/SEO, social media, sales promotion, to drive site traffic, sales and revenue;
Analyze market and in-house data to understand consumer behaviors and identify marketing trends and provide regular reports for management review.

Requirements:

Degree holder in E-commerce, Marketing or related discipline;
At least 5 years of experience in similar role;
Knowledge of eCommerce in other Asia Pacific markets is an additional advantage.
Strong planning and organizing skills;
Excellent analytical and project management skills;
Good understanding of Fashion and Retail Industry;
Familiar with mobile and web technologies, including but not limit to UI/UX, SEO, SEM, e-Commerce, P.I.M & D.A.M,  Order orchestration,  Social Media Marketing, APIs, etc.;
Good knowledge in e-Commerce system architecture and technical solutions is highly preferred
Immediate availability is preferable.
We offer competitive remuneration package, 5-day work week and career development to successful candidate. Interested parties, please submit your resume with current and expected salary Apply Now.


 * All personal data collected will be used for recruitment purpose only.

Job Descriptions


As a member for the global process management team, manage and participate in …

Define, monitor and follow-up on operational KPIs; working with global, regional and local business teams to continuously improve operational productivity and quality across the global organization;
Plan and execute global or regional processes change and improvement initiative in line with changes in regulations, market conditions, industry practices and customer needs;
Develop training material and conduct process related training (online or face-to-face depending on circumstances) for operational staff across the globe;
Participate in larger process improvement and digital transformation projects, focusing on operational processes and change management.

Qualification & experience Requirements:-

The candidates must have high intellectual capacity with a detail-oriented mindset and the ability to zoom out and look at the big picture;
Minimum 3 years of working experience , ideally in International Logistics or Supply Chain Management;
A diploma or above in a related subject such as Information Technology, Computer Science, Logistics or Supply Chain Management, is preferred;
Strong communication and analytical skills; with ability to bridge the gap between business and technology;
Training / experience in Project Management;
Experience from working with Business Process Design, Process Management and /or Process Outsourcing will be a plus;
Good command of both written and spoken English;
Immediately available preferred. 

Interested parties please send full resume with employment history and expected salary to HRA Division, Yusen Logistics Global Management Limited at Level 31, Tower 1, Kowloon Commerce Centre, 51 Kwai Cheong Road, Kwai Chung or by email to hr.ylhk @ hk.yusen-logistics.com.

Yusen Logistics Global Management Limited is an equal opportunity employer. All information collected will be used for recruitment purpose only.

Responsibilities


Be responsible for store infrastructure management of all retail stores including tools and equipment procurement, repair and maintenance;
Liaise with outsourcing partner for logistics and storage management;
Assist e-commerce daily operations, including stock transit, and providing customer services.
Requirements
Bachelor degree holder with 1-2 year(s) of experience in retail industry;
Proficient in Microsoft Office Applications and Chinese Word Processing;
Good command of written & spoken English, Mandarin, and Cantonese;
Detail-minded;
A team player with good communication and interpersonal skills.


Interest parties, please send full resume with current and expected salary and date of availability by clicking "Apply Now". Personal data provided in application will be treated as strictly confidential and used for recruitment purpose by MARYLING only. All unsuccessful applications will be destroyed upon completion of the process.

Responsibilities

Responsible for assisting in all-round HR & Administrative functions mainly in full cycle of recruitment process, compensation & benefits as well as monthly payroll processing, training & development, performance management and employee relationship;
Benchmark and recommend remuneration package for potential candidates to ensure competitiveness in the market and internal equity;
Ensure Human Resources Functions in compliance with Hong Kong Labour Ordinance and local regulations;
Review and update all HR policies and procedures in accordance with latest statutorily requirement;
Implement HR policies in compliance with labour ordinances, HQ SOP, internal policies & procedures;
Support Human Resources function, benefits administration; leave management;
Assisting in regularly reports, such as staff turnover, monthly headcount, exit interview, etc.;
Monitor and administer the office administration such as facility maintenance and repair management etc.;
Support in organizing company functions; annual dinner and staff activities;
Provide day-to-day support to the team;
Prepare monthly reports and analysis for management’s review;
Perform ad-hoc assignments.

 Requirements

Degree in Human Resources or related disciplines;

At least 6 years relevant working experience in HR function;
Well-versed in Hong Kong Employment Ordinance and related legislations
Good numerical sense, excellent data interpretation and analytical skills
Strong sense of responsibilities and commitment, well-organized, effective communications skills in interacting with people at all levels
Proficient with Microsoft Word, Chinese, Excel
Fluency in written & spoken in English and Mandarin
Able to communicate with all levels of staff

Candidates with lower qualification and experience will be considered for lower position.  Interested parties, please send full resume, availability and expected salary to our company.

All information provided by applicants will be treated in strict confidence and used only for employment-related purposes. All personal data of unsuccessful applicants will be destroyed within 6 months.

About Zeek
Zeek is the brand name under Kin Shun Information Technology Limited which incorporated in 2019. Zeek aims to provide smart logistics, SaaS solutions and online / offline integrated instant delivery service for Hong Kong and Southeast Asia market, meeting their needs for food & parcel delivery and last-mile logistics.

We strive for building an excellent delivery experience by adopting big data and artificial intelligence. With existing business in Hong Kong, Singapore, Malaysia, Thailand and Vietnam, we will continue to expand our business to Southeast Asia countries and regions like Taiwan, Philippines and Indonesia in near future.


Responsibilities:


To supervise and managing the delivery operations, particularly on workforce management strictly on company regulation to ensure the operations flow is smoothly and efficiency;
Oversees the strategy , planning .and execution of projects to  ensure accuracy  and cost-efficiency;
Experience with sortation center/ parcel fulfillment center, cost benefit analysis, labor productivity analysis in order to effectively plan and scheduling the operations resources in order to meet and exceed internal and external services levels at all times with productive and cost efficiency;
Work with related departments to maintain and enhance the platform of reward system for member activation and engagement;
Measure performance, provide a feedback as well as taking proactive steps to ensure the best practices are shared across all departments;
Create a positive and collaborative team environment by setting and regularly reviewing the achievement of team goals;
Document and track any failures/error including reporting on failure rates, causes, and preventable incidents;
Assist in training and coaching new and existing team members;
Perform ad-hoc duties / projects assigned by top management

Requirements:

Diploma holder or above in Logistics, Supply Chain Management or related disciplines;
5-7 years’ relevant experience of which 2 years were at supervisory level in operations from logistics/supply chain industries;
Experience in emerging technology in logistics and supply chain, including but not limited to open-platform, dynamic pricing; knowledge of cloud service in logistics is a plus;
Strong planning and analytical skills. Sensitive to numbers;
Good people management and presentation skills;
Independent, flexible, stress resistant and able to work in a fast pace team-base environment;
Proficiency in MS Excel, Word, PowerPoint and Chinese word processing;
Good command of both written and spoken English, Chinese and Putonghua

We offer competitive remuneration, birthday and work anniversary holidays and benefit packages to the right candidate.

Please send your detailed resume, with last and expected salary to our Human Resources Department by clicking "Apply Now”. 

(All information collected will be treated in strict confidence and used solely for recruitment)

